"{\"id\":{\"0\":\"c0\",\"1\":\"c1\",\"2\":\"c2\"},\"class\":{\"0\":\"applied\",\"1\":\"applied\",\"2\":\"applied\"},\"tocase\":{\"0\":\"Allanson v Midland Credit Ltd and Anor (1977) 30 FLR 108\",\"1\":\"Macquarie Bank Ltd v Bardetta and Ors (2005) 216 ALR 670\",\"2\":\"Re Veghelyi; Smith and Ors v Official Trustee in Bankruptcy (1993) 45 FCR 413\"},\"text\":{\"0\":\"7 The affidavit evidence discloses that there are intricate factual and legal matters, involving numerous parties, arising in the Supreme Court proceedings. This Court may grant leave under s 58(3) of the Bankruptcy Act if it considers that the issues would be better and more comprehensively dealt with by a contested trial of the action in the Supreme Court than would be the case if the applicants were required to lodge a proof of debt in respect of the bankrupt estate: see Allanson v Midland Credit Limited and Anor (1977) 30 FLR 108 at 114 per Bowen CJ, Riley and Deane JJ; Macquarie Bank Ltd v Bardetta and Ors (2005) 216 ALR 670 at [19]-[21] per Conti J.\",\"1\":\"7 The affidavit evidence discloses that there are intricate factual and legal matters, involving numerous parties, arising in the Supreme Court proceedings. This Court may grant leave under s 58(3) of the Bankruptcy Act if it considers that the issues would be better and more comprehensively dealt with by a contested trial of the action in the Supreme Court than would be the case if the applicants were required to lodge a proof of debt in respect of the bankrupt estate: see Allanson v Midland Credit Limited and Anor (1977) 30 FLR 108 at 114 per Bowen CJ, Riley and Deane JJ; Macquarie Bank Ltd v Bardetta and Ors (2005) 216 ALR 670 at [19]-[21] per Conti J.\",\"2\":\"9 For these reasons, the Court considers that leave should be granted. The applicants seek that leave be granted effective from 26 July 2005. This Court has power to make a nunc pro tunc order: see Re Veghelyi; Smith and Ors v Official Trustee in Bankruptcy (1993) 45 FCR 413. Accordingly, the Court will make the orders as sought.\\n \\n\\n I certify that the preceding nine (9) numbered paragraphs are a true copy of the Reasons for Judgment herein of the Honourable Justice Cowdroy. \\n\\n\\nAssociate:\\n\\nDated: 4 July 2006\\n\\n\\n Counsel for the Applicant: P W Flynn \\n \\n Solicitor for the Applicant: Blake Dawson Waldron \\n \\n Counsel for the Respondents: The respondents did not appear. \\n \\n Date of Hearing: 7 June 2006 \\n \\n Date of Judgment: 7 June 2006 \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n AustLII: Copyright Policy | Disclaimers | Privacy Policy | Feedback \\n URL: http:\\/\\/www.austlii.edu.au\\/au\\/cases\\/cth\\/FCA\\/2006\\/852.html\"}}"